post_cb({"4944615": {"ParentId": "4944436", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>Just cast it?</p>\n<pre><code>unsigned char *conbuf = (unsigned char *)buf;\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "468344", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "4944615", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2011-02-09T12:06:04.957", "LastActivityDate": "2011-02-09T12:06:04.957"}, "4944436": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "9948", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "238902", "CreationDate": "2011-02-09T11:47:23.543", "LastActivityDate": "2016-02-23T10:57:16.517", "Title": "Convert char array to unsigned char*", "LastEditDate": "2016-02-23T10:57:16.517", "Id": "4944436", "Score": "6", "Body": "<p>Is there a way to convert <code>char[]</code> to <code>unsigned char*</code>?  </p>\n<pre><code>char buf[50] = \"this is a test\"; \nunsigned char* conbuf = // what should I add here\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><type-conversion>", "OwnerUserId": "609625", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_4944436_4944451_0": {"section_id": 6045, "quality": 0.9, "length": 18}}, "n3337": {"so_4944436_4944451_0": {"section_id": 5813, "quality": 0.9, "length": 18}}, "n4659": {"so_4944436_4944451_0": {"section_id": 7544, "quality": 0.9, "length": 18}}}, "4944451": {"ParentId": "4944436", "LastEditDate": "2011-02-09T14:35:05.353", "CommentCount": "3", "CreationDate": "2011-02-09T11:49:12.530", "OwnerUserId": "3848", "LastEditorUserId": "3848", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "4944451", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>Although it may not be technically 100% legal this will work <code>reinterpret_cast&lt;unsigned char*&gt;(buf)</code>.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>The reason this is not 100% technically legal is due to section 5.2.10 <code>expr.reinterpret.cast</code> bullet 7.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_4944436_4944451_0\">A pointer to an object can be explicitly converted to a pointer to an object of a different type. original type yields the original pointer value, the result of such a pointer conversion is unspecified.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Which I take to mean that <code>*reinterpret_cast&lt;unsigned char*&gt;(buf) = 'a'</code> is unspecified but <code>*reinterpret_cast&lt;char*&gt;(reinterpret_cast&lt;unsigned char*&gt;(buf)) = 'a'</code> is OK.</p>\n</hr>", "LastActivityDate": "2011-02-09T14:35:05.353"}});